Package: GLOWr
Type: Package
Title: inteGrative anaLysis using Optimized Weights (GLOW) for Rare Variant Analysis
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2026-06-13
Authors@R: c(
    person("Hong", "Zhang", email = "consistencyzhang@gmail.com", role = "aut"),
    person("Ming", "Liu", email = "mliu5@wpi.edu", role = "aut"),
    person("Zheyang", "Wu", email = "zheyangwu@wpi.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
    )
Description: Implements the GLOW (inteGrative anaLysis using Optimized Weights) methodology
    for integrative variant-set association analysis with optimal weighting in
    whole-genome sequencing studies. Provides methods for Burden, SKAT, Fisher,
    and Omnibus tests with optimal weight calculation. The package supports both
    continuous and binary phenotypes with options for covariate adjustment and
    genome-wide analysis.
URL: https://zwulab.github.io/GLOWr/, https://github.com/ZWuLab/GLOWr
